-- Brazil Coffee Growers Hoarding Crop to Wait for Price Increase
-- B y   M a r i o   S e r g i o   L i m a
-- 2012-08-17T14:57:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-17/brazil-coffee-growers-hoarding-crop-to-wait-for-price-increase.html
Coffee growers in  Brazil , the
world’s largest producer and exporter, are hoarding their crops
as they wait for prices to rise, the country’s National Coffee
Council said in an e-mailed report.  Delays in the harvest are also reducing sales, CNC, as the
council is known, said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mario Sergio Lima in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 mlima11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carlos Caminada at 
 ccaminada1@bloomberg.net  